gomodel:SYNGO_2382  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Basal synaptic transmission is increased in TN-R deficient mice (Fig. 2B). In turn long term potentiation (LTP) (Fig. 3) is impaired.. Experimental description: \"Three- to four-month-old TN-R deficient mice44 with a mixed C57BL/6J×129Ola×129Sv/Ev genetic background (TN-R -/-) and wild-type littermate mice (TN-R +/+) with corresponding genotype were used in experiments\". p. 360" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
